<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{4}{x}-{2}{y}={24}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{x}+{7}{y}=-{58}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({2},-{8}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{4}{x}+-{2}{y}={24}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{4}{x}={24}-{\left(-{2}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{{24}-{\left(-{2}{y}\right)}}}{{4}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{\left(\frac{{{24}-{\left(-{2}{y}\right)}}}{{4}}\right)}+{7}{y}=-{58}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{1}}{{4}}\cdot{\left({24}\right)}--\frac{{1}}{{4}}{\left(-{2}\right)}{y}+{7}{y}=-{58}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}-{\left(-{0.5}\right)}{y}+{7}{y}=-{58}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{0.5}{y}+{\left({7}\right)}{y}=-{58}--{6}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{0.5}{y}+{\left({7}\right)}{y}=-{52}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{0.5}+{\left({7}\right)}\right)}{y}=-{52}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6.5}{y}=-{52}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{52}}{{6.5}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{8}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{4}{x}+-{2}{\left(-{8}\right)}={24}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{4}{x}+{\left({16}\right)}={24}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{4}{x}={24}-{\left({16}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{4}{x}={8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{8}}{{4}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={2}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({2},-{8}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

